sql:
SELECT user_id, username 
FROM users 
WHERE role = 'developer';

external_knowledge:
- "budding stages" here refers to projects with budgets less than 100,000.0, implying they are still in the initial or development phase; 
- "gentle hands of Jane Smith" is a metaphorical way to refer to projects last updated by the user named 'jane.smith';
- "nurturing saplings under the watchful eyes of a gardener" is used metaphorically to describe the careful management of these projects.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(user_story_id) AS num_user_stories
FROM user_stories
WHERE estimated_hours > (SELECT AVG(estimated_hours) FROM user_stories);

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT updated_by)
FROM (
  SELECT updated_by FROM tasks
  UNION
  SELECT updated_by FROM projects
);

SELECT title
FROM user_stories
WHERE estimated_hours = (
    SELECT MAX(estimated_hours)
    FROM user_stories
);

SELECT task_id, title, description, due_date, assigned_to, status, priority, estimated_hours, actual_hours
FROM tasks
WHERE user_story_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM user_stories 
WHERE created_by = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'jane.smith');

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming projects" refers to tasks;
- "require more than a week of nurturing" corresponds to tasks with estimated hours greater than 5;
- "detailed growth plans" refer to the titles and estimated hours of both tasks and user stories;
- "state of their garden" refers to the state name;
- "gardener in charge" refers to the user assigned to the task.

sql:
SELECT user_story_id 
FROM user_story_transitions 
WHERE transition_id = 3;

SELECT u.username, us.user_story_id, us.title, us.description, us.estimated_hours, us.actual_hours
FROM users u
JOIN user_stories us ON u.user_id = us.created_by;

SELECT p.project_name, w.workflow_name 
FROM projects p 
INNER JOIN workflows w ON p.project_id = w.project_id;

external_knowledge:
- Key contributors: Users who have created a significant number of projects or tasks;
- Assignments: Refers to the tasks or user stories created by each user;
- Overall workload: Total estimated effort in hours for the tasks created by a user;
- Diversity of project statuses: Variety of states associated with user stories, indicating progress stages.
